residents voted sunday on whether they want 
to turn venice into two cities cutting adrift the soggy section of 
town that tourists love but locals are leaving 
the nonbinding referendum proposes splitting venice proper the 
historic and romantic maze of canals and islands from mestre a 
bedroom community across a bridge to the mainland 
residents of both communities were voting sunday and monday and 
mestre residents outnumber venetians 31 results were to be 
announced after the completion of voting 
ten years ago a group of influential venetians lobbied for a 
similar referendum that proposal was defeated with more than 72 
percent of the voters opposed to separation 
this years referendum was pressed by mestre which has been 
steadily absorbing venices population lacking affordable housing 
young venetians have been moving to the mainland 
in 1951 venice had 175000 people while mestre had about 50000 
in 1987 venices population stood at 83000 while mestre had 
250000 
remaining venetians complaining of the scarcity of grocery 
stores go to mestre to do their shopping venices tourist 
development has been virtually unchecked with shop after shop 
converted into sourenir stores 
mestre politicians say the growing communitys needs are 
different from those of aging touristchoked venice and that 
mestres identity is overwhelmed by venices fame 
sundays referendum was consultative only a vote in favor of 
separation would have to be approved by the regional veneto 
government 
the result will be announced after the completion of voting 
monday afternoon 
also voting in a consultative referendum was the seaside city of 
ostia on whether to split from rome 17 miles inland 
