100 vehicles that had been stopped by the demonstration on the busy 
tongidhaka highway according to the sangram reporter salahuddin 
babar who was at the scene 
the shoes are manufactured by bata in bangladesh protesters say 
a stylized drawing of three bells on the inner sole of the sandal 
resembles allah in the arab script 
the problem was compounded by the fact that moslems consider the 
sole of the foot a symbol of disrespect 
bata has issued a public apology saying the designs resemblance 
to the name allah is unintentional it said the design was provided 
by a bangladeshi moslem 
about 90 percent of bangladeshs population is moslem the 
