opened fire sunday on hindus exercising in a park in northern punjab 
state killing 23 and wounding 27 according to police 
they said the gunmen also set off two bombs killing two 
policemen 
the attack occurred in nehru park in the town of moga 60 miles 
south of amritsar 
police said the victims belonged to the national selfreliance 
group which follows a strict regimen of early morning exercises 
the group is an affiliate of the bharatiya janata party a 
rightwing political organization that wants to make hinduism 
indias state religion 
sikh separatists demanding that punjab be made a selfgoverning 
sikh homeland began a campaign of violence in 1982 sikh extremists 
have been blamed for the deaths of at least 900 people this year 
with most of the victims killed in punjab 
the separatists say they are discriminated against culturally and 
economically by indias hindudominated government 
police said they did not know how many gunmen took part in 
sundays attack the victims ranged in age from 18 to 50 according 
to the police 
the bodies were scattered across the grass their khaki shorts 
and white vests soaked with blood 
press trust of india said home minister buta singh a sikh flew 
to moga to assess the situation 
authorities imposed an indefinite curfew in moga and gov 
sidhharth s ray ordered police to capture the terrorists 
responsible for the massacre dead or alive within a week united 
news of india reported 
it quoted ray as saying the perpetrators of this ghastly crime 
are neither hindus nor sikhs but animals hired by vested 
interests 
he said the vested interests were hired from across our 
border to create chaos confusion and division in our sacred land 
ray did not name any country but india accuses predominantly 
moslem pakistan of harboring and aiding sikh extremists pakistan 
has denied the allegation 
about 88 percent of indias 880 million people are hindu sikhs 
make up only 2 percent of the population but are in a slight 
majority in punjab 
sikhism is an offshoot of the hindu religion it was founded in 
northern india about 500 years ago and is based on belief in one god 
and rejects idolatry and the caste system 
