capital shelled the ports of jounieh and byblos with rounds of 
sovietdesigned 130mm mortars the ports have become the christians 
only link with the outside world 
aouns gunners opened up with 155mm howitzers on the seaside 
boulevard of west beirut where several syrian batteries are 
entrenched 
there were no immediate reports of injuries 
the syrians have harassed the besieged christian enclave since 
the latest round in the 14yearold civil war began march 8 
fighting between christian army commander gen michel aouns 
20000 soldiers and the 40000strong syrian troops began when aoun 
blockaded illegal militiarun ports because he said they cost his 
government 100 million yearly in lost revenues 
syrian troops in lebanon under a 1976 arab league peacekeeping 
mandate responded by shelling the 310squaremile christian enclave 
by police count 373 people have been killed and 1460 wounded in 
the 14 weeks of fighting several arab league calls for a 
comprehensive ceasefire have been undermined 
us secretary of state james baker has reiterated a us call 
for the lebanese to show restraint to avert further bloodshed 
moslem officials said sunday 
baker reportedly made his appeal in a letter sent to acting prime 
minister salim hoss who heads the moslem cabinet vying for power 
with a rival christian government officials at hoss office said 
the existence of the letter could not be confirmed sunday and it 
was not known whether baker sent a similar document to aoun 
police said the abducted civil servant raja bsat who works at 
the ministry of economy was freed late saturday they did not 
identify his abductors or give other details 
