an indian checkpoint near this border city 
on sunday blocked 110 tanker trucks carrying fuel to nepal hit by 
acute shortages caused by a threemonthold trade and transit 
dispute between two countries 
the 3300gallon tankers carrying gasoline kereosene and diesel 
oil from singapore were lined up at the checkpoint at raxaul in the 
eastern indian state of bihar 
shyam bihar rai the driver of one indianregistered tanker 
truck said the convoys documents were cleared by calcutta port 
customs in eastern india yet these people indian customs 
officials at raxaul are not allowing us to cross the border to 
enter nepal 
indian customs officials say each truck would be allowed to carry 
only 106 gallons of fuel in its own fuel tank to reach its 
destination in nepal one official said this was a precaution 
against possible smuggling 
but the drivers said they needed more than that in their fuel 
tanks to make the return journey to calcutta 
india and nepal have been embroiled in a dispute since march 23 
when their trade and transit treaties expired the indian government 
has closed 13 of the 15 trade points along its 1000mile border 
with landlocked nepal 
one of those still open is raxaul connected by a small wooden 
bridge with birgunj 75 miles south of katmandu 
a senior nepalese officer said the indian move to stop the 
imports from singapore was intended to further pressure his country 
