imported by nepal from a third country zonal administrative 
commissioner tek bahadur thapa told reporters it seems the action 
has been taken to create more hardships for the nepalese 
india traditionally has been a supplier of petroleum products to 
nepal but after the trade and transit agreements expired the 
indian oil corporation stopped handling petroleum products for nepal 
the resulting shortages have led to fuel rationing in nepal a 
car owner is allowed to buy only 26 gallons a week 
nepal has imported some petroleum products through neighboring 
tibet and airlifted some from bangladesh 
